  "prompt": "What are the best SEO tips for a new startup?",
  "response": "Here are some top SEO tips for a new startup:\n\n1. Keyword Research\n- Identify relevant, low-competition keywords\n- Use tools like Google Keyword Planner, SEMrush\n- Focus on long-tail keywords specific to your niche\n\n2. On-Page SEO\n- Optimize page titles and meta descriptions\n- Use header tags (H1, H2)\n- Create high-quality, original content\n- Include target keywords naturally\n- Optimize images with alt text\n\n3. Technical SEO\n- Ensure website is mobile-responsive\n- Improve site speed\n- Create a sitemap\n- Use SSL certificate\n- Implement schema markup\n\n4. Content Strategy\n- Start a blog\n- Publish regular, valuable content\n- Create evergreen content\n- Answer common customer questions\n- Use multimedia (videos, infographics)\n\n5. Link Building\n- Guest post on relevant websites\n- Create shareable content\n- Engage in industry forums\n- Build relationships with influencers\n- Use HARO (Help A Reporter Out)\n\n6. Local SEO\n- Claim Google My Business listing\n- Ensure consistent NAP (Name, Address, Phone)\n- Get local citations\n- Encourage customer reviews\n\n7. Analytics\n- Set up Google Analytics\n- Monitor key performance metrics\n- Track keyword rankings\n- Analyze user behavior",
